WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.180
Welcome back! Today we're revising Photosynthesis — how green plants make their own food.

2
00:00:07.180 --> 00:00:12.388
We'll cover the four things a plant needs, the biggest traps in this topic,

3
00:00:12.388 --> 00:00:16.000
and the exact phrases that score marks in Section B.

4
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.363
Let's start with the definition.

5
00:00:19.363 --> 00:00:26.085
Memorise this word for word: photosynthesis is the process by which green plants make their

6
00:00:26.085 --> 00:00:30.592
own food, using water, carbon dioxide, light and chlorophyll.

7
00:00:30.592 --> 00:00:35.762
So it needs four things: water, carbon dioxide, light and chlorophyll.

8
00:00:35.762 --> 00:00:40.786
And it makes two things: food, which is sugar or starch, and oxygen.

9
00:00:41.786 --> 00:00:45.376
Where does each need come from? Water comes from the soil.

10
00:00:45.376 --> 00:00:49.400
It's absorbed by the roots and carried up the stem to the leaves.

11
00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:54.909
Carbon dioxide comes from the air, and enters the leaf through tiny holes called stomata.

12
00:00:54.909 --> 00:00:59.181
Light usually comes from the Sun, and is absorbed by the chlorophyll.

13
00:00:59.181 --> 00:01:04.566
And chlorophyll is already inside the leaf — it's the green substance that traps light.

14
00:01:04.566 --> 00:01:09.519
Remember: take away any one of these four, and photosynthesis cannot take place.

15
00:01:10.519 --> 00:01:14.882
Now the biggest trap. Plants make food — they do not absorb it!

16
00:01:14.882 --> 00:01:18.969
Never write, the plant takes in food through its roots, or,

17
00:01:18.969 --> 00:01:21.254
the plant gets food from the Sun.

18
00:01:21.254 --> 00:01:26.449
Instead write: the plant makes its own food by photosynthesis, using water,

19
00:01:26.449 --> 00:01:29.080
carbon dioxide, light and chlorophyll.

20
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:33.790
The roots absorb water and mineral salts from the soil — never food.

21
00:01:33.790 --> 00:01:35.868
And light is energy, not food.

22
00:01:35.868 --> 00:01:40.647
Green plants are the only living things that can make their own food.

23
00:01:41.647 --> 00:01:46.654
The leaf is the plant's food factory, and it's perfectly built for the job.

24
00:01:46.654 --> 00:01:51.327
It's broad and flat, giving a large surface area to absorb more light.

25
00:01:51.327 --> 00:01:55.801
It's green, because it contains chlorophyll, which traps the light.

26
00:01:55.801 --> 00:01:59.940
It's thin, so carbon dioxide can reach the inner cells easily.

27
00:01:59.940 --> 00:02:04.814
And it has stomata, tiny holes that let carbon dioxide in and oxygen out.

28
00:02:05.814 --> 00:02:10.971
Why does photosynthesis matter so much? Three reasons. One: food for everyone.

29
00:02:10.971 --> 00:02:16.063
Green plants are producers — the only living things that make their own food.

30
00:02:16.063 --> 00:02:19.832
Animals depend on plants, either directly by eating them,

31
00:02:19.832 --> 00:02:23.006
or indirectly by eating animals that ate plants.

32
00:02:23.006 --> 00:02:28.957
Two: it gives out oxygen, which all living things need for respiration, to release energy.

33
00:02:28.957 --> 00:02:31.469
And three: it takes in carbon dioxide,

34
00:02:31.469 --> 00:02:35.768
helping to keep the amount of carbon dioxide in the air balanced.

35
00:02:36.768 --> 00:02:42.143
Now, the biggest trap in this whole topic: photosynthesis versus respiration.

36
00:02:42.143 --> 00:02:48.495
Photosynthesis happens in green plants only; respiration happens in all living things — pla

37
00:02:48.495 --> 00:02:49.612
nts and animals.

38
00:02:49.612 --> 00:02:55.336
Photosynthesis only happens when there is light; respiration happens all the time,

39
00:02:55.336 --> 00:02:56.313
day and night.

40
00:02:56.313 --> 00:03:01.898
Photosynthesis takes in carbon dioxide and water, and gives out oxygen and food.

41
00:03:01.898 --> 00:03:07.273
Respiration takes in oxygen and food, and gives out carbon dioxide and water.

42
00:03:07.273 --> 00:03:11.600
Photosynthesis stores energy in food; respiration releases it.

43
00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:18.784
So let's be very clear. In the day, plants photosynthesise and respire at the same time.

44
00:03:18.784 --> 00:03:24.334
At night, there's no light, so there's no photosynthesis — plants only respire.

45
00:03:24.334 --> 00:03:29.112
That means at night they take in oxygen and give out carbon dioxide.

46
00:03:29.112 --> 00:03:34.663
Never write, plants only respire at night, or, plants give out oxygen at night.

47
00:03:34.663 --> 00:03:39.300
Plants respire all the time. It's photosynthesis that needs light.

48
00:03:40.300 --> 00:03:46.339
Let's look at experiments. If a leaf has been photosynthesising, it will contain starch.

49
00:03:46.339 --> 00:03:48.534
We test it with iodine solution.

50
00:03:48.534 --> 00:03:53.475
If it turns blue-black, starch is present, so photosynthesis took place.

51
00:03:53.475 --> 00:03:58.621
If it stays brown, there's no starch, so photosynthesis did not take place.

52
00:03:58.621 --> 00:04:04.865
Now here's a favourite question: why is the plant kept in the dark for one to two days firs

53
00:04:04.865 --> 00:04:10.354
t? To remove any starch already stored in the leaves. That's called destarching.

54
00:04:10.354 --> 00:04:15.500
Then any starch found afterwards must have been made during the experiment.

55
00:04:16.500 --> 00:04:19.307
Here's the classic variegated leaf question.

56
00:04:19.307 --> 00:04:24.283
A leaf that's green in the middle and white at the edges is tested for starch,

57
00:04:24.283 --> 00:04:27.217
and only the green part turns blue-black. Why?

58
00:04:27.217 --> 00:04:31.874
The model answer: only the green part contains chlorophyll to trap light,

59
00:04:31.874 --> 00:04:35.000
so only it could photosynthesise and make starch.

60
00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:39.657
The white part has no chlorophyll, so no photosynthesis took place there.

61
00:04:40.657 --> 00:04:45.561
Another version: part of a leaf is covered with black paper for two days.

62
00:04:45.561 --> 00:04:50.936
Why does the covered part stay brown? Because the black paper blocked the light.

63
00:04:50.936 --> 00:04:56.312
Without light, photosynthesis could not take place there, so no starch was made.

64
00:04:56.312 --> 00:05:00.209
And remember the fair test rule: change only one variable.

65
00:05:00.209 --> 00:05:05.651
Keep everything else the same — the same type of plant, the same amount of water,

66
00:05:05.651 --> 00:05:08.675
the same temperature, and the same leaf size.

67
00:05:09.675 --> 00:05:14.181
Answering technique. Use these keywords: makes its own food.

68
00:05:14.181 --> 00:05:19.438
Water, carbon dioxide, light and chlorophyll. Chlorophyll traps light.

69
00:05:19.438 --> 00:05:25.371
Enters through the stomata. Gives out oxygen. Photosynthesis cannot take place.

70
00:05:25.371 --> 00:05:28.150
And, producer. Then use the formulas.

71
00:05:28.150 --> 00:05:33.257
For a missing need: without blank, photosynthesis cannot take place,

72
00:05:33.257 --> 00:05:40.091
the plant cannot make food, so it will not have enough energy to grow and will eventually d

73
00:05:40.091 --> 00:05:40.317
ie.

74
00:05:40.317 --> 00:05:47.001
For light or chlorophyll: that part of the leaf has no chlorophyll, or received no light,

75
00:05:47.001 --> 00:05:52.108
so photosynthesis could not take place there and no starch was made.

76
00:05:53.108 --> 00:05:54.693
Time to test yourself!

77
00:05:54.693 --> 00:06:01.034
Ali says, plants take in carbon dioxide and give out oxygen all the time. Is he correct?

78
00:06:01.034 --> 00:06:04.564
Pause the video and try. Ready? The answer is no.

79
00:06:04.564 --> 00:06:10.400
Plants only take in carbon dioxide and give out oxygen when they photosynthesise,

80
00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:11.697
which needs light.

81
00:06:11.697 --> 00:06:18.254
At night there is no light, so plants only respire — they take in oxygen and give out carbo

82
00:06:18.254 --> 00:06:18.975
n dioxide.

83
00:06:19.975 --> 00:06:20.831
Let's recap.

84
00:06:20.831 --> 00:06:26.327
Photosynthesis: green plants make their own food using water, carbon dioxide,

85
00:06:26.327 --> 00:06:30.252
light and chlorophyll, and it produces food and oxygen.

86
00:06:30.252 --> 00:06:36.461
Water comes from the soil through the roots, carbon dioxide enters through the stomata,

87
00:06:36.461 --> 00:06:38.745
and chlorophyll traps the light.

88
00:06:38.745 --> 00:06:43.884
Roots absorb water and mineral salts, not food — plants make their food!

89
00:06:43.884 --> 00:06:47.595
The leaf is broad and flat for a large surface area.

90
00:06:47.595 --> 00:06:50.522
Remove any one need, and no food is made.

91
00:06:50.522 --> 00:06:54.875
Plants respire day and night, but photosynthesis needs light.

92
00:06:54.875 --> 00:07:01.370
And for the starch test: blue-black means photosynthesis took place — and destarch the plan

93
00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:01.941
t first!

94
00:07:02.941 --> 00:07:09.365
You've got this! Remember: plants make their own food, and they respire day and night.

95
00:07:09.365 --> 00:07:15.191
Use the keywords and the answer formulas, and those Section B marks will grow.

96
00:07:15.191 --> 00:07:19.375
Good luck with your revision, and all the best for PSLE!
